----
title: LOHAS RGB A19 E26 60W PWM 
date-published: 2019-19-19
type: light
standard: us
----

## Notes
 This is for the LOHAS blubs that are PWM based and not based on the my92x1 chips. 
 Amazon link - https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07T7W7ZMW/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_asin_title_o04_s00?ie=UTF8&psc=1
 
 ## GPIO Pinout
 
| Pin     | Function      |
|---------|---------------|
| GPIO5   | Red Channel   |
| GPIO4   | Green Channel |
| GPIO13  | Blue Channel  |

## Basic Configuration
'''yaml
esphome:
  name: lohasrgb
  platform: ESP8266
  board: esp01_1m

wifi:
  ssid: ssid
  password: password


  # Enable fallback hotspot (captive portal) in case wifi connection fails
  ap:
    ssid: ssid
    password: password

captive_portal:

# Enable logging
logger:

# Enable Home Assistant API
api:

ota:



# Individual outputs
output:
  - platform: esp8266_pwm
    id: output_red
    pin: GPIO5
 #   frequency: 10 hz
  - platform: esp8266_pwm
    id: output_green
 #   frequency: 100 hz
    pin: GPIO4
  - platform: esp8266_pwm
    id: output_blue
    pin: GPIO13
    inverted: false
 #   frequency: 50 hz
light:
  - platform: rgb
    name: "Lohas RGB"
    red: output_red
    green: output_green
    blue: output_blue
 
